This article is a press gaggle by Principal Deputy Press Secretary Josh Earnest and Deputy National Security Advisor Ben Rhodes. They give a readout of the G7 meetings and discuss the main topics that were discussed. They mention that all G7 countries are aligned in their messages to Russia, particularly regarding the recognition of the election in Ukraine and the need for Russia to cease its support for separatist elements in the east. They also discuss the importance of energy and climate, global health security, and the global economy. They mention that sectoral sanctions are on the table if Russia continues to escalate the situation in Ukraine. The article also briefly touches on the topic of Sergeant Bergdahl and the concerns of some military members regarding his rescue. Finally, they discuss the role of the G7 in advancing talks on a climate deal.